<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf67a5fcc-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7112"><num value="7112">§ 7112.</num><heading> Licenses of masters or mates as pilots</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A master or mate licensed under this part who also qualifies as a pilot is not required to hold 2 licenses. Instead, the qualification of the master or mate as pilot shall be endorsed on the master’s or mate’s license.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf67a5fcd-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/541">97 Stat. 541</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
